[32m│[0m ### thoughts                                                                                                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Why this approach worked:**                                                                                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. The application has inconsistent authorization checks - GET requests are properly protected, but POST requests lack ownership validation          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. The `is_admin` field appears disabled in the UI (client-side protection) but the backend accepts the parameter value                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. JWT token contains the company ID in `sub` claim, but the backend doesn't validate the URL parameter matches the token subject                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Key security flaws identified:**                                                                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - No server-side validation that the authenticated company ID matches the requested profile ID in POST requests                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Mass assignment vulnerability allows setting `is_admin` field                                                                                      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Security through obscurity (disabled dropdown) rather than proper access control                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                                                                                                      [32m│[0m
